      <description>Nathaniel Patrick Perry was born March 17, 1912, in New Orleans, La., and
            grew up in Baton Rouge. He attended Baton Rouge Colored High School and graduated from
            McKinley High School in 1930. He received a B.A. degree in mathematics from New Orleans
            University (now Dillard University) in 1935. Perry received degrees in divinity and
            social work from Howard University and spent most of his career as a minister. He was
            also an accomplished singer, performing with the Louisiana Bards Male Chorus of New
            Orleans University at the 1933 World's Fair in Chicago. He married Clytie Fears of
            Alexandria, La., and died June 15, 2002.</description>
   </name>
